      ],
      "parameters": [
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "A pointer to the destination in memory where the drawing is to be rendered. The size of this memory block should be at least ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "(bytesPerRow*height)",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " bytes.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Pass ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "NULL",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " if you want this function to allocate memory for the bitmap. This frees you from managing your own memory, which reduces memory leak issues.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "data"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The width, in pixels, of the required bitmap.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "width"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The height, in pixels, of the required bitmap.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "height"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The number of bits to use for each component of a pixel in memory. For example, for a 32-bit pixel format and an RGB color space, you would specify a value of 8 bits per component. For the list of supported pixel formats, see “Supported Pixel Formats” in the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "devLink-1719830",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " chapter of ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "devLink-1719815",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ".",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "bitsPerComponent"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The number of bytes of memory to use per row of the bitmap. If the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "data",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " parameter is ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "NULL",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": ", passing a value of ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "0",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " causes the value to be calculated automatically.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "bytesPerRow"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "The color space to use for the bitmap context. Note that indexed color spaces are not supported for bitmap graphics contexts.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "colorspace"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Constants that specify whether the bitmap should contain an alpha channel, the alpha channel’s relative location in a pixel, and information about whether the pixel components are floating-point or integer values. The constants for specifying the alpha channel information are declared with the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgimagealphainfo",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " type but can be passed to this parameter safely. You can also pass the other constants associated with the ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgbitmapinfo",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": " type.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "For an example of how to specify the color space, bits per pixel, bits per pixel component, and bitmap information, see ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "identifier": "devLink-1719830",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "type": "reference"
                },
                {
                  "text": ". ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "bitmapInfo"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "A new bitmap context, or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "NULL",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " if a context could not be created. You are responsible for releasing this object using ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/1586509-cgcontextrelease",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "When you draw into this context, Core Graphics renders your drawing as bitmapped data in the specified block of memory.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The pixel format for a new bitmap context is determined by three parameters—the number of bits per component, the color space, and an alpha option (expressed as a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgbitmapinfo",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " constant). The alpha value determines the opacity of a pixel when it is drawn.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
